        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued April 5 at 11:22AM CDT by NWS Fort Worth TX</headline>
        <description>At 1121 AM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Mart, or 12 miles east of Bellmead, moving northeast at 50 mph.

HAZARD...Penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Minor damage to outdoor objects is possible.

This strong thunderstorm will be near...
Dawson around 1140 AM CDT.

Other locations impacted by this storm include Silver City, Watt,
Dresden, Axtell, Pelham, Mount Calm, Navarro Mills, Prairie Hill,
Purdon, and Richland.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
